        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 11:52PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1152 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Abbeville, or 6 miles north of Troy, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coronaca, Bradley, Greenwood, Promised Land, Ninety Six Historic
Site, Ninety Six, Epworth, Troy, and Callison.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
Upstate South Carolina.</instruction>
